snippet.textDisplay:
A few tips!
Aggression is key. Don't let the posture bar recover. Keep attacking, but don't spam, always be ready to deflect.

Remember to use stealth. Multiple enemies will kill you fast. Ceramic Shards is very useful for separating enemies.

Don't be afraid to try to deflect instead of dodging. Almost everything can be deflected, but dodging will most often get you killed. Also mind the direction of the incoming attack. Horizontal attacks can be avoided by jumping.

Make sure to search every nook and cranny. There's a lot of very useful items easily missed. And take note of the eavesdrops. You'll learn many tips for beating bosses, completing quests and where to go.

Hope you'll keep playing. This is just about the best combat you'll ever find, but the learning curve is steep!
Love your content and hope to see more of Sekiro on your channel.
You won't regret it.

snippet.textDisplay: Rogue/Souls like games are not my cup of tea, especially, since I am an explorer, a hoarder, a builder, a crafter and a collector and hate losing half my items. On top of that, I'm an Action RPG loving adventurer, which Sekiro is lacking, but not every game can nor should be like Skyrim, even though, those are my preferred types of games that I am always searching for to purchase and play. Lastly, a morality system with choices and consequences and a ton of side quests and side activities is a must in the games I play. For those who love straight up combat with a bit of exploration and don't mind dying thousands of times, then this is the perfect game for them. It's a 6/10 game for me. To each their own!
